"title": "5483: punishment, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5483",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Punishment is the inevitable and equitable consequence of breaking the law of God. In keeping with God's justice and righteousness, punishment is administered by him or by human beings as his agents.</p>\n<h2>God warned Adam and Eve of the punishment for disobedience</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:16-Gen2:17\">GEN 2:16–2:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:1-Gen3:5\">GEN 3:1–3:5</a></p>\n<h2>Adam and Eve's original disobedience brought inevitable punishment</h2>\n<h3>Upon the serpent</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:14-Gen3:15\">GEN 3:14–3:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:15\">COL 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:9\">REV 12:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:1-Rev20:3\">REV 20:1–20:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:10\">REV 20:10</a></p>\n<h3>Upon the woman</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:16\">GEN 3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps48:6\">PSA 48:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:8\">ISA 13:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa21:3\">ISA 21:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:31\">JER 4:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:14-1Tim2:15\">1TI 2:14–2:15</a></p>\n<h3>Upon the man</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:19\">GEN 3:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:7\">JOB 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:1\">JOB 7:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:5\">PSA 90:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:7\">PSA 90:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:8\">PSA 90:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl1:3\">ECC 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:2\">ISA 40:2</a></p>\n<h3>Upon creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:17\">GEN 3:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:29\">GEN 5:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:4\">JER 12:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:19-Rom8:22\">ROM 8:19–8:22</a></p>\n<h2>The punishment of death</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:23\">ROM 6:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:4\">EZK 18:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:8\">EZK 33:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:12\">ROM 5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:21\">ROM 6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:21-1Cor15:22\">1CO 15:21–15:22</a></p>\n<h2>Banishment as punishment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:23\">GEN 3:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:10-Gen4:16\">GEN 4:10–4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:27\">DEU 29:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:28\">DEU 29:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:21\">2KI 25:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:12\">MAT 8:12</a></p>\n<h2>Punishment must be appropriate to the crime</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:6\">GEN 9:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:23-Exod21:25\">EXO 21:23–21:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev24:17-Lev24:22\">LEV 24:17–24:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:24\">JDG 9:24</a></p>\n<h2>Punishment reflects the obligations of the offenders towards their victims</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:3\">EXO 22:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:2\">EXO 21:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:26-Exod21:27\">EXO 21:26–21:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:4-Exod22:9\">EXO 22:4–22:9</a></p>\n<h2>Divine punishment is always totally just</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:25\">GEN 18:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:4\">GEN 20:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:7\">EXO 34:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:35\">DEU 32:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:23\">2CH 6:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:11\">ISA 3:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:27\">MAT 16:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:12-1Cor3:15\">1CO 3:12–3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:6\">1TH 4:6</a></p>\n<h2>God appoints human agents to administer his punishment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:4\">ROM 13:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:1\">ISA 45:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:14\">ISA 45:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:20\">JER 51:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:13\">MIC 4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:13-1Pet2:14\">1PE 2:13–2:14</a></p>",
